<TEXT>
snapping turtles are feeding off ducks 
at a town pond but duck lovers are getting even by feasting on the 
turtles 
the strongjawed turtles in douglas pond have been latching onto 
ducks by the feet dragging them under water and eating them said 
crowley fralick who works at a nearby sporting goods store in 
bluefield 
it is their way of survival i understand that fralick said 
friday 
still it got to be a little much during the spring when the 
young ducklings started disappearing he said the little ones 
are easy for the turtles to catch 
fralick and his coworkers have responded by trapping the 
turtles in the oneacre pond and turning them into soup in three 
years theyve caught and eaten 72 snappers 
last year was the first time i tried one it was pretty good 
really it was delicious fralick said 
</TEXT>
