taylor is prolonging the war 
sources said today that johnsons rebels recently attacked 
taylors forces deep behind their lines cutting a main supply 
route johnson had pulled some men out of monrovia for the surprise 
attacks said the sources who visited the area and spoke on 
condition of anonymity 
the attacks were launched in nimba county about 300 miles from 
the capital the rebels first began their invasion seven months ago 
in nimba county which borders the ivory coast 
diplomats confidently told reporters weeks ago that as soon as 
rebels were spotted in monrovia they expected does troops to flee 
like many other observers they believed does illtrained and 
poorly paid army would continue a pattern of retreat set in the 
early months of the campaign the rebels had encountered little 
resistance as they advanced hundreds of miles from liberias 
northeastern border with the ivory coast to monrovia in the 
southwest 
they finally slowed down as they entered hostile country and 
left behind territory populated by sympathizers who fed them hid 
them and informed on government troop movements 
guerrilla warfare training learned in libya and burkina faso was 
of little use in the seesaw street battles the rebels fought with 
does forces in the rundown capital 
civilian recruits have bolstered taylors forces from the 200 
who invaded from ivory coast in december to the more than 10000 
troops hes believed to command now but most like does soldiers 
have little training hundreds are boys barely in their teens 
for more than a month reporters traveling with the rebels have 
reported they are as ready to drop their arms and run as the 
government troops 
