<TEXT>
lawmakers clashed today over a measure to 
restructure the strategic defense initiative within the 1991 
defense bill with one democratic sponsor arguing that the 
amendment gives president bush clear guidance on the program 
in a frantic rush to finish the 289 billion defense bill and 
adjourn for a summer recess the senate tackled the thorny issue of 
sdi commonly known as star wars and the administrations request 
of 47 billion for the program 
the senate armed services committee in approving its bill last 
month trimmed about 1 billion from bushs budget proposal for the 
fiscal year beginning oct 1 
the most contentious issue was an amendment sponsored by sens 
jeff bingaman dnm and richard shelby dala to restructure 
sdi with the emphasis on groundbased systems rather than the 
spacebased brilliant pebbles system now in development 
a key proponent of the program republican sen malcolm wallop 
