by saying the council would meet again if necessary to consider 
further steps to ensure compliance in un parlance that means 
the council is prepared to impose sanctions if the demands of the 
resolution are not met 
pickering said the united states seeks sweeping sanctions 
covering economic trade financial and military aspects the 
military measures would include an embargo on arms military 
supplies training and equipment but would not cover the 
possibility of deploying un or international troops to force iraq 
to withdraw from kuwait 
