here at a glance is a comparison of 
president bushs proposed spending for various military weapons and 
the changes approved by the senate on saturday and the house armed 
services committee on tuesday 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed spending 307 billion on defense the senate 
approved a 289 billion defense bill for the fiscal year beginning 
oct 1 the house panel adopted a 283 billion bill actual 
spending must be done through separate appropriations bills 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
in january bush called for a total of 55 billion for five 
planes next year and advanced procurement money for 10 planes the 
following year defense secretary dick cheney announced a revision 
in april that proposed two planes in 1991 and advanced procurement 
of six planes in 1992 at a cost of 46 billion the senate agreed 
with the revised plan the house panel eliminated all procurement 
money and included only enough funds to cancel the program after 
the 15 planes currently under development 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed 47 billion for the program commonly known as 
star wars the senate cut nearly 1 billion for a total of 37 
billion the house committee slashed close to 2 billion for a 
total of 29 billion 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the presidents request included 16 billion for procurement 
and military construction costs and 548 million for research 
involved with moving the mx nuclear missile from fixed silos to 
railroad cars the senate approved only the research money the 
house panel eliminated all money for the program and instead 
created a fund of 610 million for advanced missile work calling 
on bush to decide in 90 days what it should be used for the mx or 
the unbuilt midgetman 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bush proposed 202 million in research money for the mobile 
singlewarhead missile the senate approved the request the house 
committee eliminated the funds in favor of the 610 million 
strategic missile pot 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
bushs budget cancels the tiltrotor aircraft that takes off 
like a helicopter but can fly like a plane the senate added 238 
million in research money for the plane the house committee 
included the research money as well as 165 million in procurement 
funds 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
the administration proposed a reduction of about 38000 from the 
current total of 21 million military personnel the senate adopted 
a cut of 100000 including 50000 in europe the house committee 
approved a reduction of 129500 
