against iraq including blocking iraqi assets and prohibiting 
import into japan of all goods and services of iraqi origin and 
make these sanctions both mandatory and comprehensive 
frank coleman a spokesman for damato said that kimura the 
deputy chief of mission at the embassy accepted the letter but was 
noncomittal in his statements 
he said that kaifu had talked to bush and that no options 
were precluded coleman said of kimura the dcm said he 
couldnt say specifically what course of action would be taken 
but that an announcement would be made 
a white house statement issued after a bush meeting with top 
advisers at camp david md saturday said that japan along with 
west germany and france had decided to join the united states in 
freezing kuwaiti assets in order to stop iraq from confiscating 
them 
but kaifu has said that japan would impose sanctions against 
iraq only if the united nations votes to do so 
damatos office said that japan gets 8 percent of its imported 
oil from iraq and 59 percent from kuwait 
describing his meeting with kimura damato said he told the 
