in what may be the first time a government 
has been sued for the movement of a glacier the united states has 
agreed to pay the husband of a woman killed when ice fell on her in 
kenai fjords national park 
thais grabenauer 59 of napa calif died one day after the 
june 16 1987 accident during the couples outing to the 
spectacular exit glacier 
according to a national park service investigation mrs 
grabenauer was standing beneath overhanging ice while her husband 
ken stepped away to take a photograph half a ton of ice broke off 
and knocked both of them to the ground 
rangers flew mrs grabenauer to anchorage where she died in a 
hospital of internal injuries 
the lawsuit filed two years later by ken grabenauer charged the 
park service with negligence for failing to warn visitors 
adequately of the hazards of glacier ice and for failing to erect 
barriers 
park service officials admitted no liability in the outofcourt 
settlement reached in march both parties agreed not to disclose 
the amount of the settlement 
