<TEXT>
the senate approved a 289 billion defense 
bill saturday that cuts 1 billion from president bushs request 
for the strategic defense initiative but leaves intact his fiscal 
1991 proposal for two b2 bombers 
in a rush to finish before a summer recess the senate adopted 
7916 a military budget that slashes 18 billion from bushs 
request of 307 billion for the fiscal year beginning oct 1 
we have developed a manageable and prudent and responsible 
reduction in defense expenditures related to the threat senate 
armed services chairman sam nunn dga said shortly before the 
chamber approved one of the first military budgets in the postcold 
war era 
the senate package adopted despite the threat of a presidential 
veto calls for a military personnel reduction of 100000 and 
elimination of 16 billion in procurement money for the mx 
railgarrison missile program 
the white house has said defense secretary dick cheney would 
recommend a presidential veto because of the sdi total and troop 
cuts the objection comes even though the senate bill is considered 
the high mark in congress 
the house when it returns in september will likely approve its 
committees version of a 283 billion defense bill 
senators lingered as legislative loners in the capitol as house 
members commenced their august recess in the early morning hours 
during a marathon session they passed campaign finance reform 
legislation a bill containing assistance for areas hardest hit by 
aids cases and an environnmental protection measure arising from 
the exxon valdez oil spill off alaska 
shortly before adjourning until sept 10 the senate also passed 
a bill appropriating roughly 28 billion for transportation 
programs for the new year including money for upgrading the 
nations airports mass transit systems and amtrak 
and sources said that an intelligence budget for 1991 passed by 
voice vote during the previous postmidnight session eliminates 
us support for a covert war in cambodia and sharply restricts 
money for rebels in afghanistan many of the details in the bill 
are secret since it authorizes some of the nations most sensitive 
covert operations 
passage of the defense bill came after the senate voted to 
restructure the sdi program commonly known as star wars by 
delaying deployment of the brilliant pebbles concept 
by a vote of 5444 the senate approved a restructuring 
amendment that leaves intact the chambers approved total of 37 
billion for sdi 1 billion less than bush proposed 
however the measure scales back the administrations request 
for the brilliant pebbles concept from 329 million to 129 million 
nunn criticized the pentagon for trying four different systems 
for the sdi program in the past three years while congress hasnt 
received one clue from anybody in this administration on how to 
pay for the antimissile shield 
no one can tell you where the moneys coming from and yet 
theyre charging straight ahead nunn said noting the likely 
annual cost of 10 billion for sdi 
the amendment comes on the heels of a congressional report that 
found deploying the first phase of sdi in 1993 would be premature 
and fraught with high risk 
the general accounting office the investigative arm of 
congress said that the introduction of brilliant pebbles has 
drastically changed the sdi systems design leaving it in a state 
of flux the technology involves several thousand interceptors that 
would orbit the earth to seek and destroy a target by smashing into 
it at high speeds 
a key sponsor sen jeff bingaman dnm said the amendment 
would be rejecting early deployment of systems that would violate 
the antiballistic missile treaty 
the senate later rebuffed two attempts to reduce the sdi budget 
even further including one that would have cut the 1991 budget to 
about 3 billion 
the defense bill deletes money for two ssn21 seawolf attack 
submarines replacing the request with two ssn688 los 
angelesclass attack submarines and delays the c17 transport 
aircraft program 
the bill also provides 238 million in research money for the 
v22 osprey tiltrotor aircraft a program defense secretary dick 
cheney has tried to kill for the past two years 
during three days of lengthy sessions the senate adopted by a 
narrow margin the presidents request for 46 billion for two b2 
stealth bombers in fiscal 1991 despite eroding support for the 
costliest aircraft in history at 865 million a copy the senate 
left intact bushs budget proposal but required the program to pass 
critical tests before money could be spent 
the senate decision sets up a confrontation with the house armed 
services panel which agreed to halt the program at the 15 
radarevading planes in development 
the bill also eliminated 16 billion in procurement money 
requested in fiscal 1991 for the program to put mx nuclear missiles 
on railroad cars the senate left intact the 548 million for 
research on the system as well as the 202 million for the 
midgetman landbased nuclear missile 
the house armed services committee eliminated the 
administrations request for both missiles and instead set up a 
strategic pot of 610 million for the two weapons the panel also 
called on bush to decide which missile he wants 
the legislation calls for a cut of 100000 military personnel 
including 50000 from us troop strength in europe where the 
committee believes the threat of a largescale warsaw pact attack 
against western europe has virtually been eliminated 
the nations troop strength currently totals 21 million a 
number certain to decrease significantly in light of bushs plan 
announced thursday to reduce us forces 25 percent over the next 
five years 
among the measures approved by the house and senate late friday 
and early saturday were these 
a house democratic leadershipbacked version of a campaign 
finance package majority democrats pushed aside proposals from 
both republicans and from within their own party and prevailed 
255155 
the bill which now has to be reconciled with a senate version 
would among other things limit house campaign spending to 715000 
per candidate 
a bill boosting the liability of shippers for the cost of 
cleaning up oil spills and requiring new tankers to have 
leakresistant double hulls 
a measure providing more than 4 billion over five years to 
help communities hardest hit by aids 
emergency legislation providing the treasury department with 
72 billion in additional borrowing authority through oct 2 
an intelligence budget for 1991 that eliminates us support 
for a covert war in cambodia and sharply restricts money for rebels 
in afghanistan according to congressional sources 
