mission which would last about a month the navy declined to 
comment on the ships movements 
the navy in a response forwarded by senior chief journalist 
gene romano at sand point naval station in seattle acknowledged 
that the upkeep period has been a demanding time with significant 
effort required of the crew 
pressure to accomplish the work safely and on schedule is 
naturally present but is no different from what a crew must 
routinely contend with whether in port or in combat training at 
sea it said under these circumstances a lot is asked of 
and given by these dedicated individuals and it is 
understandable that they sometimes look for outlets to let off 
steam 
the navy said the reported allegations are vague and there are 
few specifics on which to base a response however performance 
standards on nimitz are very high and a continuing program of crew 
training testing and qualification is conducted with extensive 
oversight widespread cheating is not possible 
