<TEXT>
a sustained rise in oil prices due to iraqs 
invasion of kuwait and speculation about further aggression 
threatens a global economic slowdown higher inflation and rising 
interest rates experts say 
however the industrial world is much less vulnerable to oil 
shocks than it was in the 1970s when arab oil embargoes rattled 
western economies they said 
the situation will be different even in the worst case 
scenario it is unlikely that oil prices will jump on a sustained 
