<TEXT>
northwest airlines moving to counter rising 
jet fuel prices said friday it will add a flat oneway surcharge 
of 8 to the price of domestic tickets beginning aug 9 
the surcharge stems directly from increases in jet fuel costs 
incurred by the carrier since iraqi troops invaded oilrich kuwait 
said northwest spokesman bob gibbons 
this will give us a chance to see what happens in the next few 
days gibbons said this is not intended to be a permanent 
increase and its certainly adjustable 
fuel prices have jumped 8 cents a gallon and are expected to 
rise even higher because of uncertainty in the persian gulf 
gibbons predicted other airlines would follow northwests lead 
as jet fuel costs continue to rise the effect of the uncertainty 
in the middle east is clear it packs a pretty big wallop he 
said 
the surcharge will be reviewed periodically and could jump even 
higher said gibbons 
he said northwest is also considering adding a similar surcharge 
to its international flights fuel surcharges do not require 
governmewnt approval for domestic flights 
fuel costs are a major contributor to the operating expenses of 
all airlines said jack van der wege senior director of fuel 
administration crude oil prices have jumped considerably since 
wednesday and will be sharply higher in august than was previously 
anticipated 
fuel is northwests secondlargest cost accounting for about 17 
percent of its operating expenses in january the eaganbased 
carrier announced similar surcharges to offset rising jet fuel 
costs but withdrew them additional before they went into effect 
